cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper deals with image segmentation using convolutional neural networks and data augmentation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves learning a model of transformations, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the use of unlabeled scans in a semi-supervised approach could also place it in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the task of segmenting magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) brain scans could also make it relevant to cs.MM (Multimedia).
